-- Indian, Chinese Cement Makers Seek Stakes in Kenyan Companies, Daily Says
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-10-18T06:27:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/indian-chinese-cement-makers-seek-stakes-in-kenyan-companies-daily-says.html
Chinese and Indian companies are
seeking stakes in  East Africa Portland Cement Co.  and  Athi River
Mining Ltd. ,  Business Daily  reported, citing people it didn’t
identify.  Jedong Development Group, Gleen Investments and  Aditya
Birla Nuvo Ltd.  expressed an interest in the stakes, the
Nairobi-based newspaper said.  Lafarge SA , the world’s biggest cement maker, currently
owns 41.7 percent of East African Portland, 58.6 percent of
 Bamburi Cement Co.  and 4 percent of Athi River, it said. Sanghi
Cemtech of India and Catic Cement of China are currently
building manufacturing plants in Kenya, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Eric Ombok  in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 